    <!-- Help Screen -->
    <string name="help_screen_title">HELP MODULE</string>
    <string name="help_screen_desc">Step-by-step guide to master SafeMe - SOS and protect yourself in risky situations.</string>
    <string name="help_step_by_step">STEP BY STEP: APP FUNCTIONALITY</string>
    <string name="help_step1_title">1. Configure Your Safety Profile</string>
    <string name="help_step1_desc">Enter your personal details (Name, ID, Email) and register the numbers of your emergency contacts for WhatsApp (with country code, without the + sign).</string>
    <string name="help_step2_title">2. Activate the SOS Alert</string>
    <string name="help_step2_desc">In case of emergency, go to the \'SOS Button\' tab and press and hold the center button. The system will immediately geolocate your exact GPS coordinates in real time.</string>
    <string name="help_step3_title">3. Send WhatsApp Alerts</string>
    <string name="help_step3_desc">Once the alert is started, the active report panel with the registered contacts will appear. Press the green button to instantly send them a structured WhatsApp message. This message includes your name, ID, incident type, risk level, a Google Maps link with your exact location, and Gemini AI safety recommendations.</string>
    <string name="help_step4_title">4. Monitor Severity Levels</string>
    <string name="help_step4_desc">The app uses a dynamic escalation system: YELLOW (low), ORANGE (medium), RED (high), and BLACK (critical without signal). Coordinates are automatically updated with each severity change.</string>
    <string name="help_step5_title">5. Safety Check Verification</string>
    <string name="help_step5_desc">During an active alert, the app will show you a dialog asking \'Are you still safe?\'. If you do not respond before the timer, the severity will automatically escalate and the SOS will be updated.</string>
    <string name="help_step6_title">6. Confirm You Are Safe</string>
    <string name="help_step6_desc">When the emergency has passed, press the \'I AM SAFE!\' button. This will stop the SOS alert and timer, and allow you to send a predefined peace-of-mind message to your contacts via WhatsApp.</string>
    <string name="help_step7_title">7. Emergency Numbers Lookup</string>
    <string name="help_step7_desc">In the \'Numbers\' tab, you will have access to the local database of emergency numbers for the country you registered in your profile (Police, Firefighters, Ambulances, etc.), ready to call.</string>

